  <div class="ct">
  
<p>And I will be the first to confess that I haven't studied the facts of the case sufficiently &nbsp;to evaluate the Court's arguments, so I will play a little Rebecca of SunnyBrook Farm here knowing that I could be wrong, wrong, wrong...</p>
<p>On its face, I've always been bothered that the law seems to have frozen a set list of jurisdictions over the years -- especially when you see big complaints in the last election come out of places like Ohio and Philadelphia. It does have a little luck of punishing the south for old news while ignoring dirty laundry in northerly climes.</p>
<p>The thing that really seems questionable about the latest renewal of the act -- and something different from earlier iterations -- was the length of the extension. 25 years. &nbsp;That's a long time to freeze special circumstances into place.</p>

